node.text:
Yooo! My own brand has a billboard in times square (and in subways stations across Brooklyn and manhattan)with MY face on it! 19 year old Brad who had just moved to nyc with big hopes and dreams would be so proud. I spent so many years confused, wondering if what I wanted to accomplish would actually happen. I even remember in my first year living here, broke as hell, I had missed my train home at 4am and I couldn’t afford to take a taxi home. The next train wasn’t for 40 more mins, so I sat there baling my eyes out, ready to accept defeat. I was over the city. I felt like I kept getting chewed up and spit out. But times like those is what pushed me to achieve even more. I got up after crying, brushed my pants off and said to myself “ew bitch that was so embarrassing”  then continued to kick ass. I’ve learned that the true secret to success is getting back up every time you fall, no matter how many times. 

And thank YOU, all of you, for supporting me and my brand. If you spot me around nyc tag me in your pics and I’ll repost them! 

Love you! 
Brad

node.text:
My dad passed away on 4.22.2021 after living with the Parkinson’s for many years. He influenced my life greatly. From my career, to my extreme drive for success, and even my sense of style. Like, did you see those photos of him from when he was younger? FASHION ICON. 

I’ll never forget the day I walked into his office at the salon he owned and told him I would one day, when I’m older, move to NYC and create my own haircare line. He told me “boy, you’re crazy”, which was completely accurate. I am crazy. I was told that up to his final months he would watch my videos on youtube and comment about my hair and the peoples hair I was reacting to. Like father like son. He never lacked having a strong opinion on everything. I’m so happy he got to see that his craziest son was able to achieve all he promised he would.

He engrained so many quotes into my head like, “you don’t get nothin’ for nothin’ ” and “keep it simple stupid” along with an array of outlandish curse word combinations that I will never forget. My dad was the shit, is the shit and will always be the shit. 

Throught this entire experience seeing my dad pass, I am reminded to live my extra fucking life. Cause you only have one life and you have no idea how short it really is until it’s over. 

Love you dad ♥️

If you’d like to donate to the Michael J. Fox foundation for Parkinson’s research please do so with the link in my bio.
